So now our rationale is &quot;hey, at least we're better than Saddam&quot;?  We KNOW he was a bad guy.  When the hell did I ever suggest we take him out for beers and smoke a few Cubans with him?  Shooting civilians at anti-American rallies doesn't do too too much when you're trying to raise Iraqi public opinion.  (Yes, public opinion and the resistance are pretty closely linked.  The less they like us, the more likely some of them are to support opposition fighters.  Not because they want Saddam back; because they would want us out.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fuck the cost, first of all. If I have to pay an extra hundred bucks in taxes this year because of the war, I have no problem with that. Second, 300 deaths is an insanely small cost compared to the number of deaths that could have happened.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, you don't mind the extra $100 dollars in taxes, however you were behind this war from the beginning.  You might not view 300 deaths as a large cost, but I view it as 300 people that wouldn't have died had we not lauched this war- not to mention the estimated 4,000 Iraqi civilians who died due to the war.  (Yes, Saddam probably would have killed more, but I really don't think we should be judging ourselves in terms of &quot;hey, we're better than Saddam!&quot;)<br>
<br>
That 4,000 figure is an Amnesty International estimate, take it for what you will,  they are certainly a liberal organization but they strive hard to get their facts straight.  U.S. officials refuse to make an estimate, saying any deaths were accidental and therefore a collateral damage estimate isn't necessary.  No, I'm not making that up.  So much for magnamity.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Then you'd be a shortsighted fool, is all. For my part, if I were an Iraqi, it'd only take one tour of one of Saddam's electric torture chambers before I'd support the Americans for as long as they needed to stay.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You seem to be under the impression that not only did Iraqis not know about these torture chambers, but that we'd be better for the Iraqis than any attempts at government they can set up in the short term.  Saddam's gone, and more than likely dead.  The torture chambers don't get used anymore.  I really don't think people in the Middle East buy that we're doing this purely of our own magnamity; we have our own interests involved here.  They are not obliged to kiss our ass because we decided to topple our government.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have no love for Grimstaff, believe me, but, yes, if Grimstaff's thread made him a prick, then this thread makes you a prick. And I seriously doubt Grimstaff said anything about sunshine and lollipops. I for one knew this would be a long and tough road. Sorry if anyone made you think otherwise.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
a) I know I'm a prick, that was half the point of the post.<br>
b) You must not have read his posts, because almost every time he was confronted with a question he didn't have an immediate answer for, the response was &quot;just wait and see, everything's going to turn out fine&quot;.  In fact, that's the kind of crap which led to his &quot;Still Waiting&quot; post, and hence this post.<br>
c) Well, the Pentagon did say they expected to be out of Iraq within a year.  Most of the 3rd Infantry was supposed to be back home by now, but their stay has been extended indefinitely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valtser>Valtser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice... forever!</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Politica`Mon</span><hr size=1> Politica'Mon I CHOOSE YOOOOOOOOOUU <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzadikandinsky>KilzadiKandinsky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 411<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 1:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Politica`Mon</span><hr size=1> To you I say Claud, WHO CARES? they're in no danger, in fact they're having a nice vacation in Iraq, helping the people(I'm sure the red cross hasn't the numbers to help an ENTIRE COUNTRY) and they get paid for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melcar>melcar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1133<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 1:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Politica`Mon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> they're in no danger<hr></blockquote>